Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 01:29:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] pace: 0022 S1-guided rewind actuator (both decode loops,
 dedicated buffers, E-DET profiles)

ANCHORED TO THE CANONICAL v2 CHAIN + 0027 + 0028 (base github.com/antirez/ds4
@80ebbc3 + patches/ds4/canonical/ 21 patches -> ds4.c md5 1db4f799, + 0027 +
0028 -> md5 62ed2e71; byte-identical to the live-tree pace0028 target, pod2
canonical_build_v2). Applies AFTER 0028; rebase after further pace canonization.

The PRODUCTION actuator for the prevention->correction->airbag ladder
(docs/S1_REWIND_DESIGN.md), replacing the 0027 R1 diagnostic. It fixes the two
coverage lessons the pod2 R1 smoke exposed:
  (a) the 0027 hook lived only in ds4_session_eval_internal, muted for the
      greedy CLI path (generate_metal_graph_raw_swa) -> 0022 drives its actuator
      from BOTH decode loops (like 0028), so it is live in production greedy
      A/B, not just the session/server path;
  (b) the spec_* frontier buffers are MTP-gated (the greedy loop allocs with
      enable_mtp=false) -> 0022 allocates its OWN spec_rewind_* buffer set,
      gated on DS4_PACE_REWIND, independent of MTP being built or on, and never
      clobbered by the speculative verifier between arm and fire.

Mechanism (OFF by default; DS4_PACE_REWIND=0). Two halves:
  - DETECTOR (host, ds4_pace_rewind_detect, run from ds4_pace_s1_update): the
    tuned E-DET aggregate EWMA-CUSUM (runs/ds4/20260710_edet_s1_detector_tuning)
    on the per-token aggregate S1 (pruned/total router mass, same PRE-bias
    readback S1/0012/0026 share, FEED_AUDIT). One alpha=0.50 EWMA front-end
    feeds two one-sided CUSUMs, sigma self-calibrated over the first CALWIN tok,
    lagged-window baseline (BASE_LAG 32, BASE_WIN 128): ARM (k=0.5,h=4, cheap)
    and FIRE (k=1.0,h=8, expensive).
  - ACTUATOR (ds4_pace_rewind_after_eval, GPU, both loops, after each eval):
    while ARM is quiet it takes/refreshes a rolling frontier snapshot every
    EVERY tok (spec_rewind_* + onset logits + full PACE-accumulator blob incl
    mass/rmass/bmass/admit + rings/clocks); ARM freezes it at the last healthy
    onset. On FIRE (or the n-gram airbag as an independent fire source, gated on
    a confirmed ARM so the flat aggressive regime falls through to the airbag
    STOP), if the onset is inside the raw-ring slack (raw_cap-raw_window-GUARD)
    it restores the frontier + PACE accumulators, relearns the mask from the
    healthy-segment stats and widens to REWIND_KEEP (=keep_max), restores the
    onset logits and rewinds the loop to onset+1 (no re-prefill). Anti-
    oscillation: REWIND_MAX (2) + doubling BACKOFF (256). JSONL events
    rewind_arm / rewind / rewind_skip {from,to,reason} on DS4_PACE_LOG for the
    client-side stream retraction (S1_REWIND_DESIGN section 4); regenerated-
    token counter.

Scope (binding): SLOW-EROSION regime only (K91-family mild/wide static masks);
the aggressive W50+K23+rotate32 regime never arms (S1 flat) and correctly falls
to the airbag STOP. Rewind target is the frozen healthy checkpoint (frontier
floor = snapshot pos; MARGIN is realised by the rolling-checkpoint freeze at
ARM, not by rewinding below the snapshot). NOT yet covered: temp>0 RNG snapshot
(greedy argmax only), MTP-on speculative multi-accept across a rewind, dynamic-
mask relearn exactness under the window. Pending pod smoke.

Env (all DS4_PACE_REWIND*, off by default): master REWIND; detector ALPHA(0.5)
ARM_K(0.5) ARM_H(4) FIRE_K(1.0) FIRE_H(8) CALWIN(128) BASE_LAG(32) BASE_WIN(128);
actuator EVERY(32) MARGIN(16) MAX(2) BACKOFF(256) GUARD(32) KEEP(0=>keep_max).
Requires DS4_PACE=1 + DS4_PACE_S1=1 (the monitor). Off by default; the airbag
stopper stays the independent fallback.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
